name: Civil Unrest in Egypt
description: The U.S. embassy in Cairo closed to the public Tuesday amid civil unrest across Egypt. Some 51 people have died in the violence since Friday, and at least 128 people were injured in overnight clashes that continued into Tuesday morning.

name: Southern Storms - Tuscaloosa
description: On April 27th, the city of Tuscaloosa, Alabama was struck by an EF-4 level tornado with winds reported up to 190 mph. Leaving a scar nearly 6 miles long, 5,000 homes were were destroyed or severely damaged and 43 people lost their lives.

name: Joplin, MO
description: An EF-5 multiple-vortex tornado struck the town of Joplin, Missouri the evening of May 22nd. One of the deadliest tornadoes in U.S. history, at least 141 people were killed with an estimated 2,000 buildings destroyed.

name: South Korea landslides - Chuncheon
description: Torrential rainfall has triggered flooding and a landslide in Chuncheon killing 16 people according to the National Emergency Management Agency.

name: Wallow Fire - Arizona
description: According to InciWeb, the Wallow Fire is burning actively in eastern Arizona near the communities of Nutrioso and Alpine. Size is estimated at 233,522 acres.

name: South Korea landslides- Seoul
description: In Seoul, the heaviest rains in a century have led to flooding and landslides. At least 67 people are dead or missing.

name: Flood in Seychelles
description: Parts of the Seychelles have declared a state of emergency after severe weather hit the country.  No casualties have been reported, but flooding, landslides and rock falls have hit the main island of Mahe.

name: Flooding in Senegal
description: Six people drowned or were killed by falling structures over the weekend, after a torrential rain lashed Senegal, causing houses to crumble and neighborhoods to flood under the rushing water.

name: Jiangxi Flooding - Huanggang
description: Flooding has displaced thousands of people.

name: Jiangxi Flooding - Xiangyang
description: Flooding has displaced thousands of people.

name: Jiangxi Flooding - Xianning
description: Flooding has displaced thousands of people.

name: Jiangxi Flooding - Xiushui
description: Flooding has displaced thousands of people.

name: Tropical Cyclone Tembin
description: Tembin, the 14th storm of the Pacific typhoon season, is packing winds of 119 kph, with gusts of up to 155 kph, and has a radius of 150 km, the bureau said.

name: Souris-Missouri River Flooding - Offutt
description: Collection AOIs are defined for Minot ND, Sioux City IA, Offut and Fort Calhoun, NE.

name: Tropical Cyclone Kai-Tak
description: At least 27 people have been killed during a typhoon which swept across northern provinces of Vietnam over the weekend, officials have said.

name: Tropical Storm Leslie Over Bermuda
description: The National Hurricane Center reports Leslie was located about 660km south-southeast of Bermuda with maximum sustained winds of 110kph. Before downgrading to tropical storm status, Leslie spent two days as a Category 1 hurricane over the Atlantic.

name: Wildfires in Central Washington
description: More than 2,000 firefighters have contained about 30% of fires that cover 42,508 acres near Wenatchee.  The Table Mountain Fire near Cle Elum, meanwhile, is at 30,484 acres and 10% contained, with a high potential for further growth.

name: Wildfires in Northern Idaho
description: Several wildfires continue to burn in Northern Idaho.  The McGuire Fire Complex, Wesley Fire and Sheep Fire are currently burning in and around the Nez Perce and Payette National Forest.

name: Ponderosa Fire, California
description: Firefighters were starting to gain the upper hand Tuesday on a fire that has burned almost 20,000 acres in Northern California, with the blaze 35% contained.

name: Shockey Wildfire, California
description: The Shockey Fire has burned roughly 3,000 acres near the Shockey Truck Trail and the Campo Indian Reservation and is moving east, according to Cal Fire officials. One person has died and 30 homes have been burned.

name: Plane Crash in Nigeria
description: A passenger plane with about 150 people on board has crashed into buildings in a densely populated district of Nigeria's main city of Lagos.

name: Fires in California
description: According to data provided by the U.S. Forest Service, wildfires had burned 276,252 acres across the state as of last week, excluding the large Rush fire on the Nevada border.

name: Pipeline Explosion
description: An explosion hit a pipeline just west of the city of Homs on February 15, 2012.

name: Explosion in Brazzaville, Congo
description: Huge explosions at an arms depot, which killed at least 146 people in Congo's capital, Brazzaville, were caused by a short-circuit that led to a fire, government officials say.

name: Bomb Blast in Kano, Nigeria
description: A suicide car bomb attack at a bus stop in the Nigerian city of Kano has killed at least 22 people, police say. No group has admitted responsibility, but Islamist Boko Haram militants have previously attacked Kano.

name: Tropical Cyclone Saola-12
description: From 28/07/2012 to 30/07/2012, a Hurricane/Typhoon > 74 mph (maximum wind speed of 194 km/h) SAOLA-12 was active in NWPacific.

name: Flood in Russia
description: At least four people have been killed overnight in flash floods in Russia's Black Sea region, officials said Wednesday.

name: Artillery pounds Homs
description: Artillery positioned outside of Homs began shelling the neighborhood of Baba Amr in February.

name: Homs sees worst shelling in months
description: Aircraft and artillery continue to pound the Homs neighborhood of Al Khaldiyah.

name: Shelling of Jouret al-Shayah
description: Many clinics in the Homs neighborhood of Jouret al-Shayah were targeted and destroyed in late June/early July.

name: Wildfires in Northern Idaho
description: The Mustang Complex fire which was started by a lightning strike on the weekend of July 28-29 is currently only 16% contained and over 261,000 acres have been affected. Meanwhile, the Sheep Fire is almost 14,000 acres and is 10% contained.

name: Floods in Russia
description: The death toll from this weekend’s catastrophic flash floods in southern Russia has climbed to at least 171 people, and authorities warn that figure is likely to increase.

name: Tropical Cyclone ISAAC
description: Tropical Storm Isaac strengthened on Friday as it took aim at flood-prone Haiti, but it was not expected to become a hurricane until it barreled into the Gulf of Mexico early next week.

name: Heavy Rain in Japan
description: Heavy rain triggered flash floods and mudslides in southern Japan on Thursday, causing at least 15 deaths and leaving 11 more people missing.

name: Floods in Northern India
description: Three waves of devastating floods in India's northern state of Assam have left nearly 4.89 million displaced.  Flooding began in June this year and continued through September. 27 districts had been affected.

name: Floods in India
description: Almost one million people have been forced to leave their homes by floods in India as torrential rains lash the north-eastern state of Assam, officials say.

name: Attack on US Consulate, Benghazi
description: Gunmen attacked U.S. consulate offices in Libya's eastern city of Benghazi on Tuesday, and fought with security forces in protest against a U.S. film they say is blasphemous, a security official said.

name: London 2012 Summer Olympics
description: The 2012 Summer Olympic Games, officially the Games of the XXX Olympiad, also known informally as London 2012, is scheduled to take place in London, United Kingdom, from 27 July until 12 August 2012.

name: Wildfire in Spain
description: Four people, three French nationals and one from Spain, have been killed in forest fires raging in the Spanish region of northern Catalonia.

name: Tropical Cyclone Vicente-12
description: Vicente, this year's eighth typhoon, made landfall near the city of Taishan in Guangdong province early Tuesday, bringing gales and rainstorms to Guangdong and Guangxi.

name: Demonstrations in Cairo, Egypt
description: One demonstrator was killed and 62 injured during massive demonstrations on Sunday in Cairo’s Tahrir Square in celebration of the announcement of Mohamed Morsy as Egypt’s new president, the Ministry of Health said Monday.

name: Poco Fire, Arizona
description: The Poco Fire burning in the Tonto National Forest six miles northeast of Young, Arizona, is now 15% contained and has burned a total of 1,500 acres.

name: U.S. Open Golf Championship
description: The United States Open Championship, known as the U.S. Open, is the annual open golf tournament of the United States. It is the second of four major championships in golf, and is on the official schedule of both the PGA Tour and the European Tour.

name: Floods in Taiwan
description: Torrential rain brought floods to counties in numerous parts of the country, forcing thousands of people to evacuate their homes.

name: Refugee Crisis in Afgooye, Somalia
description: The UN refugee agency said on Tuesday some 14,000 Somalis have been displaced from Afgooye, about 30km northwest of Mogadishu, as a result of military activity in the area which started a week ago.

name: Refugee Crisis in Rayhanli, Turkey
description: Nearly 400 Syrians poured into Turkey in the last 24 hours seeking refuge amid a recent surge in violence in the strife-torn country, a Turkish official said Saturday.

name: Reported Massacre in Qubair, Syria
description: Activists said pro-government militia men and security forces killed at least 78 people, including children, in Syria's central province of Hama on Wednesday.

name: High Park Fire, Colorado
description: At least 18 structures have been burned in the fast-moving High Park Fire, which has consumed about 14,000 acres, forced hundreds of people to evacuate their homes and spewed plumes of smoke so thick they hide the Rocky Mountains.

name: EURO 2012
description: The 2012 UEFA European Football Championship, will be the 14th European Championship for national football teams organized by UEFA. The final tournament is being hosted by Poland and Ukraine between 8 June and 1 July 2012.

name: Wildfire in New Mexico
description: Two lightning-sparked blazes that merged in a mountainous southwestern New Mexico forest are close to becoming the largest wildfire in state history, fire officials said Tuesday.

name: Joplin, MO - 1 yr Anniversary
description: An EF-5 multiple-vortex tornado struck the town of Joplin, Missouri the evening of May 22nd. One of the deadliest tornadoes in U.S. history, at least 141 people were killed with an estimated 2,000 buildings destroyed.

name: Volcanic Eruption in Guatemala
description: On Saturday, Fuego Volcano began erupting lava and ash prompting alerts and flight restrictions in the nation's capital of Guatemala

name: Terrorist Attack in Sanaa, Yemen
description: More than 90 people have been killed in a suicide bomb attack at a military parade rehearsal in Yemen's capital, Sanaa, defence ministry officials say.

name: Concordia Cruise Wreck
description: Italian rescuers have found five more bodies inside the stricken cruise ship Concordia, raising the confirmed death toll to 11.

name: Wildfires in Arizona and Colorado
description: Wildfires in Arizona and Colorado spread on Tuesday as firefighters faced problems with rugged terrain and, in some areas, wind.

name: Flood in Gansu Province, China
description: At least 49 people were killed and 23 others were missing as of Saturday after hail and torrential rain hit Northwest China's Gansu province on Thursday.

name: Formula One - Spanish GP
description: McLaren's Jenson Button beat Red Bull's Sebastian Vettel to set the fastest time in Friday practice at the Spanish Grand Prix.

name: Terrorist Attack in Damascus, Syria
description: A terrorist attack with twin suicide car-bomb attacks have killed at least 55 people and wounded 372 in Damascus, Syrian officials say.

name: Floods in Paraguay
description: Heavy rain, which began in March, has caused the Pilcomayo river in Paraguay to overflow; resulting in flooding throughout the country. An estimated 13,000 families have been isolated due to the floods.

name: Tornado in Kansas
description: A tornado hit Wichita on Saturday night as a series of storms tore through central Kansas.

name: Earthquake in Indonesia
description: A massive earthquake struck off the coast of the Indonesian island of Sumatra Wednesday afternoon, triggering a tsunami watch for the Indian Ocean, which was later canceled.

name: North Korean Launch
description: North Korea plans to launch a satellite using a carrier rocket in April, the country's official news agency said Friday, a move that would violate U.N. Security Council demands.

name: Tornado in Texas
description: Rescuers plan to search the Dallas area again Wednesday for anyone trapped after violent tornadoes flattened homes, sucked up tractor-trailers and sent debris swirling in the air.

name: Flood in Fiji
description: Severe flooding in the Pacific island nation of Fiji has killed four people and left 800 people seeking shelter in evacuation centers, a government official said Monday.

name: Lower North Fork Fire, Colorado
description: Authorities have sent out a pre-evacuation notice to 6,500 homes after a spot fire flared up one mile northwest of Waterton Canyon.

name: Coup in Mali
description: Renegade soldiers in Mali declared Thursday that they have seized power in the West African nation and dissolved public institutions because of the government's handling of an insurgency.

name: Earthquake in Mexico
description: A strong earthquake rattled residents in Mexican resort towns and the nation's capital Tuesday, but there were no immediate reports of serious damage or injuries.

name: Explosions in Damascus, Syria
description: Deadly explosions rocked parts of Damascus on Saturday with some of the targets being Syrian government facilities, witnesses and state television reported.

name: Heavy Floods in Ecuador
description: A state of emergency was declared Thursday for five Ecuadorian provinces where floods triggered by winter rains have left 20 people dead and 2,823 displaced.

name: US Midsection Tornadoes
description: A swarm of tornadoes tore through the U.S. midsection on Friday, splintering homes, damaging a prison, overturning trucks and killing at least four people in the hard-hit state of Indiana, officials said.

name: Senkaku/Diaoyu Islands Dispute
description: Two Chinese-government vessels reached waters near the disputed Senkaku islands as Beijing continued directing angry rhetoric at Tokyo, a day after Japan announced plans to purchase three of the islands from private owners.

name: Yakima Complex Fire, WA
description: Lightning strikes have sparked more than 100 wildfires in eastern Washington since Sunday.  The Yakima Complex Fire, which includes portions of Yakima and Kittitas Counties, consists of many small fires burning on local, state and federal land.

name: Flood in El Tarf, Algeria
description: The death toll from floods in El Tarf, last Wednesday, rose to three killed. On Friday, the body of a 26-year-old man was swept away, the Civil Defense said.

name: Flood in Mozambique
description: Mozambique struggled with the destruction of a portion of its main national highway, cut-off communications and a reported death toll of 18, according to the nation's National Institute for Natural Disasters.

name: Philippines Earthquake
description: At least 15 people have died after a 6.7 magnitude quake struck the central Philippines, according to government officials.

name: One-Year Anniversary of Tahrir Square Protests in Cairo, Egypt
description: Thousands of Egyptians are holding a rally in Cairo's Tahrir Square marking the first anniversary of the uprising which toppled President Hosni Mubarak.

name: Boko Haram Bombing in Kano, Nigeria
description: Co-ordinated attacks by Islamist militants in the northern Nigerian city of Kano on Friday killed at least 160 people.

name: Syria Protests
description: The Syrian authorities have responded to widespread anti-government protests with overwhelming military force. The protests pose the greatest challenge to four decades of Assad family rule in the country.

name: Protests in Cairo, Egypt
description: Clashes have again erupted in the Egyptian capital as security forces continue their efforts to clear Cairo's Tahrir Square of protesters. At least 20 people are reported to have died since the violence began on Saturday with hundreds more injured.

name: Fire in Reno, Nevada
description: Thousands of northern Nevadans fled their homes as a massive and sudden wildfire raged out of control on Friday, consuming Sierra Nevada foothills and spreading down to the valley floor.

name: Dubai Airshow 2011
description: Aircraft orders over $47 billion have been booked at the Dubai Airport Expo, the largest event of its kind in the Middle East. More than 1,000 companies from 50 countries have converged on Dubai's International Airport this week for the exhibition.

name: Flooding in Brazil
description: Heavy rains have caused flooding and landslides in the states of Minas Gerais and Rio de Janeiro.

name: Earthquake in Italy
description: Thousands of people left homeless by a powerful earthquake in northern Italy have spent the night in shelters as aftershocks continue to hit the region.

name: The Hajj
description: An estimated 2.5 million people will make the annual Islamic pilgrimage to Mecca, Saudi Arabia. It is a religious duty for every Muslim who is able to make the pilgrimage once in their life.

name: Champions League Final - Munich, Germany
description: Chelsea stunned Bayern Munich in a dramatic penalty shoot-out at the Allianz Arena to win the Champions League for the first time.

name: Tropical Cyclone Bolaven
description: Typhoon Bolaven killed at least eight people as it lashed the Korean peninsula with strong winds and heavy rain, capsizing fishing boats and grounding aircraft.

name: Peru Earthquake
description: On October 28th a 6.9 magnitude earthquake struck Ica Province in Peru. The provincial capital was most affected with more than 100 buildings destroyed.

name: Kenyan Incursion into Somlia
description: Kenyan troops have moved into Somalia in an attempt to contain violence along its border. Recent kidnappings of aid workers and tourists have been linked to al-Shabaab, reportedly operating from the town of Afmadow.

name: Tropical Cyclone Evan
description: Tropical Cyclone Evan passed over Samoa, Wallis, and Futuna between December 13th and 16th 2012. Most of the damage caused was to infrastructure, roads, and crops.  Relief efforts are underway.

name: Hudson Volcano
description: The Chilean government has issued a red alert for residents living within 40km of Cerro Hudson. It last erupted in 1991 causing millions of dollars in damage.

name: Turkey Earthquake
description: At least 230 are dead and 1300 are injured after earthquake after a 7.2- magnitude earthquake devastated parts of eastern Turkey.

name: Flood in Bangkok
description: Thailand's capital was braced for unprecedented flooding Wednesday, amid the monsoon rains that have overwhelmed much of the country

name: Rena Oil Spill, New Zealand
description: Officials say 350 tonnes of oil may have leaked from the 775ft (236m) Rena, which ran aground on the Astrolabe Reef off the port of Tauranga on Wednesday.

name: Flood in el-Bayadh, Algeria
description: Torrential rains have caused flooding in el-Bayadh, Algeria. At least a dozen people have been killed and hundreds of homes have been destroyed.

name: Chemical Plant Fire - Texas
description: A fire at a Magnablend chemical plant on Monday Oct. 3rd, forced the evacuation of nearby schools and residences. The plant was destroyed, but there were no casualties.

name: Flooding in Niger
description: At least 44 people have been killed and thousands more made homeless after heavy floods caused the Niger River to overflow earlier this week, flooding parts of the capital Niamey and other areas

name: Suicide Car Bomb in Mogadishu
description: A huge suicide attack near government buildings in the Somali capital, Mogadishu, kills at least 70 people and injures many more, local officials say.

name: Ethnic Clash in North Kosovo
description: Several people have been injured in a clash between ethnic Serbs and Nato peacekeepers in the north of Kosovo.

name: Typhoon Nesat
description: Powerful typhoon Nesat made landfall in the Philippines, causing severe floods in Manila. The death toll rose to 18 with 35 still missing after heavy rain and powerful winds triggered storm surges.

name: Pakistan Flooding
description: For the second year in a row, Sindh province has been devastated by monsoonal flooding. An estimated 8 million people are affected.

name: Flood in Cambodia
description: Flooding in Cambodia has killed over 200 people since early September. Thousands of people have evacuated as the increasing flood situation has caused massive damage.

name: Yemen Protests
description: Dozens of protesters have been killed in the last few days. Reports out of Sana'a suggest that governments forces are shooting and shelling protest camps. Violence has erupted around the country.

name: Indian State of Sikkim Earthquake
description: At least 11 people -- six in India and five in Nepal -- died when a magnitude-6.9 earthquake struck the northern Indian state of Sikkim near the border between the two nations Sunday night

name: Nairobi Pipeline Explosion
description: At least 75 people have been killed and more than a 100 injured in the slums surrounding the Lunga Lunga industrial area following a gas pipeline explosion.

name: Transition in Libya
description: The National Transitional Council has been negotiating with Gaddafi loyalists for their peaceful surrender.

name: Texas Fires
description: More than 1,000 homes have been destroyed by recent fires in Texas and thousands have been evacuated. An estimated 85 fires are now burning.

name: Typhoon Talas
description: At least 50 people are missing and 37 people have been killed by the storm, which made landfall on Shikoku Island, triggering floods and landslides throughout Japan. Talas is currently the most destructive Typhoon since 2004.

name: Seleka Rebels Seize Capital Bangui, Central African Republic
description: Rebel forces arrived on the outskirts of Bangui on Saturday.  13 South African soldiers were killed defending the capital. Following the takeover, the African Union has suspended CAR and imposed sanctions on Seleka's leaders.

name: Tropical Cyclone Evan over Fiji
description: Tropical Cyclone Evan hit Fiji on December 17th 2012 as a Category 4 cyclone.  Evan is the largest cyclone to hit Fiji in 20 yrs.  Currently no casualties have been reported.

name: Hurricane Sandy storm damage, Haiti
description: Hurricane Sandy tore through the Caribbean between 26-28 October, leaving a reported 51 dead in Haiti and another 15 missing. The country's housing and terrain are particularly vulnerable to flooding.

name: Flooding in Nigeria
description: Over a hundred people have been killed and at least 1,500 people are displaced by torrential rain in the Oyo state capital of Ibadan. Water overflowing a dam washed away settlements.

name: Burning Man
description: The 25th annual Burning Man Festival kicked off on Monday in the Black Rock desert 100 miles north of Reno. This year's theme is "Rites of Passage."

name: Uganda Landslide
description: Dozens have been killed and dozens are still missing in Bulambuli after a landslide following torrential rains.

name: Fall of Tripoli
description: Rebels have entered Tripoli and are fighting Gaddafi loyalists for control of the Libyan capital.

name: MAKS-2011 Air Show
description: Over 200 military and civilian aircraft will be on display at the MAKS Air Show, including the Airbus A380, Boeing's 787 Dreamliner, and of particular note, the public unveiling of Sukhoi's T-50, Russia's next-generation stealth fighter.

name: Horn of Africa Famine
description: The worst drought in over 60 years has created a famine in the Horn of Africa. Millions of people have been impacted and hundreds of thousands have been displaced.

name: Syrian Protests
description: Syrian security forces continue operations to crush protesters throughout the country. An estimated 1,400 people have been killed since March.

name: Burning Man 2012
description: San Francisco cleared out considerably over the weekend as tens of thousands of artists, dreamers, hippies, techies, corporate professionals, newcomers and veteran Burners made a mass exodus to Nevada for the annual festival.

name: Vulcan del Fuego Eruption
description: Authorities ordered the evacuation of more than 33,000 people in 17 communities following the eruption of Vulcan del Fuego.  Thick clouds of ash reduced visibility to less than 10 feet in the area of sugar cane fields surrounding the volcano.

name: Wacken Open Air 2012
description: At least 75,000 heavy metal fans from 35 different countries descended on the tiny northern German town of Wacken, for the world famous Wacken Open Air Festival which will see more than 130 bands on seven stages.

name: Floods in Canada
description: More than 340 people have been ordered out of their homes in the community of Sicamous in the British Columbia Interior after heavy rains sent water and mud flowing through the streets.

name: Flood and Ocean Storm in Madagascar
description: Torrential rain has flooded large parts of Madagascar following the passing of Tropical Cyclone Irina on 01 March 2012.

name: Flood in Peru
description: On Friday, intensive rain caused collapses in bridges over the Ilave River, in Peru, and the resulting flooding caused damage to houses, along with several deaths and crop loss. The waters left many isolated.

name: Earthquake in Guatemala
description: Thirty-nine people have been killed and many more are missing after a 7.4-magnitude quake hit off the Guatemala's Pacific coast, the nation's president has said.

name: Tasmania Fire
description: Bushfires have burned about 29,000 hectares in southeast Tasmania. High heat and strong winds persist and scores are coming to grips with the destruction. In Dunalley, 65 homes and an elementary school were destroyed.

name: Noble Fire, Oklahoma
description: The Noble fire in Cleveland County, south of Oklahoma City, affected about 7,800 acres and had destroyed 25 structures -- including homes and outbuildings -- as of Saturday, officials said.

name: Wildfires in California
description: Fires have yet to relinquish their grip on northern California forests. The Fort Complex Fire began with a lightning strike on August 5 and now a month later over 23,000 acres have been affected and the fire is 30% contained.

name: Mount Soputan Eruption
description: One of Indonesia's most active volcanos has erupted, shooting ash and smoke nearly 1½ kilometers (1 mile) into the sky.

name: Volcanic Eruption in New Zealand
description: Scientists in New Zealand are monitoring Mount Tongariro carefully after the volcano erupted last night for the first time in 115 years.

name: Pine Creek Fire, Montana
description: The Pine Creek Fire has burned approximately 8,000 acres south of Livingston and over 400 people remain on the scene to work the fire.

name: Tropical Cyclone Sanba
description: A powerful typhoon lashed North and South Korea with strong wind and heavy rain Monday, killing at least one person, leaving dozens of others homeless and cutting power to many homes and businesses in the South.

name: Sziget Festival 2012
description: Placebo, LMFAO, The Killers and over 150 groups from Hungary, Europe and further afield will grace the stages at Budapest’s 20th Sziget Festival on Aug. 6-13, one of Europe’s most popular music events.

name: Flooding in Pakistan
description: Torrential rain, which began on September 5th, has caused flash floods in Pakistan leaving an estimated one million people homeless. Over 100 people have been reported killed in the floods, and many homes and properties have been inundated.

name: Explosion in Indiana
description: Authorities from various Indianapolis, Indiana and federal agencies scoured the rubble Sunday searching for clues to just what caused a massive and deadly explosion late Saturday night on the Far-Southside of the city.

name: Fires in Ecuador
description: 22 fire fighters were wounded in Ecuador after an arson attack on Tuesday. The worst affected provinces are Pichincha, El Oro and Azuay. Eight provinces were issued with an Orange alert. No victims have been reported.

name: Floods and Landslides in India
description: On Friday, a series of cloudbursts struck the Himalayan state of Uttarkhand, triggering flash floods and landslides. At least 45 people have been killed and 35 others are missing whilst several more are injured.

name: Japan Flooding - Sanjo and Tadami
description: Record rainfall in the eastern Niigata/western Fukushima prefectures have led to the advised evacuation of nearly 300,000 people.

name: Hurricane Irene
description: Currently rated a Category 2, Hurricane Irene may become a Cat 3 by the time it makes landfall near North Carolina's Outer Banks Saturday morning, drenching the East Coast as far north as Boston.

name: UN Nigeria HQ Bombing
description: A car bomb hit the UN's headquarters in Abuja, Nigeria. At least 18 people have died. The Boko Haram have claimed responsibility.

name: Floods in the Philippines
description: On Tuesday, torrential rains flooded the Philippines capital, Manila. Nine people were found dead buried under a landslide in Quezon City.

name: Waldo Canyon Fire, Colorado
description: The Waldo Canyon fire, which officials here called "very aggressive," spread in three directions and displaced about 11,000 people from their homes as fires continued to burn statewide Sunday.

name: Flooding in Italy
description: Two days of heavy rains followed by strong winds have left parts of central and northern Italy submerged.  Rising water levels have caused power cuts and transport disruptions as well as forcing some to flee their homes.

name: Floods in Northern Cameroon
description: Extreme floods have devastated Northern regions of Cameroon. Nearly 20 people have died and thousands more are left homeless. Continuous rainfall and release of the Ladgo Dam caused the Benoe River to burst its banks, flooding residential areas.

name: Earthquake in Iran
description: Relief operations are under way in Iran after two strong earthquakes in the north-west left at least 250 people dead and more than 2,000 injured.

name: Floods in South Sudan
description: Floods which began in June have been affecting the Upper Nile state in South Sudan. The flooding in Sudan has displaced over three thousand people, and at least 15 people have been reported killed.

name: Souris-Missouri River Flooding - Sioux City
description: Collection AOIs are defined for Minot ND, Sioux City IA, Offutt and Fort Calhoun, NE.

name: Souris-Missouri River Flooding - Minot
description: Collection AOIs are defined for Minot ND, Sioux City IA, Offut and Fort Calhoun, NE.

name: Fires in North Algeria
description: An estimated 20,000 hectares of land have been ravaged by forest fires in the north of Algeria since June. These are a result of hotter than average summer heat waves that have been reported to reach as high as 50 degrees Celsius.

name: Earthquakes in Southern China
description: Two quakes measuring 5.7 and 5.6 on the Richter scale hit a border area near Yiliang county in Yunnan and Weining county in Guizhou province.  An estimated 100,000 people have been evacuated and approximately 20,000 houses were destroyed.

name: Grounded Shell Oil Rig
description: The oil rig "Kulluk" ran aground on Monday after drifting in stormy weather as it was being towed.  The rig is grounded on the south-east side of Sitkalidak Island, and does not appear to be leaking at present.

name: Pemex Gas Pipe Explosion
description: The blaze in the town of Zapotlanejo was caused by a digger striking the pipeline late on Thursday, and has not yet been brought under control.  The accident injured two firefighters and an employee of the state-owned energy company Pemex.

name: Pueyhue Volcano Complex
description: Eruptions in the Puyehue-Cordon-Caulle volcano range have disrupted air traffic in Chile and Argentina. According to reports, an estimated 4,000 people have left the area.

name: In Amenas Hostage Crisis
description: Heavily armed gunmen attacked the In Amenas gas field complex in Algeria. Militants took Algerian and foreign workers hostage in the living area and the main gas facility of the Tiguentourine complex.

name: Oil Refinery Fire, Venezuela
description: Venezuelan firefighters struggled to contain the last fire at the South American country’s largest oil refinery after a second flare-up at a fuel storage tank.

name: Formula One - Hungarian GP
description: McLaren's Lewis Hamilton took his second victory of the season as he beat Lotus driver Kimi Raikkonen in the Hungarian Grand Prix.

name: Sectarian Violence in Meiktila, Myanmar
description:
Three days of rioting and arson attacks have swept through the streets
of Meiktila. Security forces, which during decades of military rule
brutally suppressed any signs of unrest, seemed unable or unwilling to
stop the rioting.

name: Christmas Island - Vessel breaks in two
description: Rough weather on Christmas Island has broken the MV Tycoon in two.

name: Red and James Rivers - Grand Forks
Red and James Rivers - Dell Rapids
California fire - Lion
description: The Lion fire in the Sequoia National Forest has grown to 11,411 acres.

name: California fire - Eagle
description: The Eagle fire, 85km ENE of San Diego on the Los Coyotes Indian Reservation has grown to 13,700 and is now 45% contained.

name: Solomon Islands, Earthquake and Tsunami
description: A powerful earthquake off the Solomon Islands generated a tsunami up to 1.5 metres (5ft) high that damaged dozens of homes and left several people missing, presumed dead.

name: Flooding in Yemen
description: Flooding in Yemen has led to 19 reported deaths, said the Yemeni Meteorology Center on Sunday. The Yemeni meteorology center warned of more heavy rains to come, especially in mountainous regions including Sana'a, Amran, Mahweet, Dhamar and Raima.

name: Severe Flooding in Buenos Aires, Argentina
description: More than 50 people have died after one of the heaviest storms recorded caused flash floods in Buenos Aires and La Plata. Thousands have been evacuated from their homes and dozens are still stranded, local media report.

name: Red River Flooding in Upper Midwest, USA
description: A potential for exceeding moderate and major river flood levels exists for the Red River of the North, which forms the state line between eastern North Dakota and northwest Minnesota for spring 2013.

name: Earthquake in Iran
description: A 6.3 magnitude earthquake has killed at least 37 people and injured 850 in south-west Iran, officials say.

name: Chelyabinsk Meteor Strike, Russia
description:
A meteor crashing in Russia's Ural mountains has injured at least 950
people, as the shock-wave blew out windows and rocked buildings.

name: Tornadoes in Arkansas and Missouri
description: Tornadoes spread mayhem in parts of Missouri and Arkansas, and now it's time for the Southeast to brace itself for possible severe weather.

name: Cyclone Haruna, Madagascar
description: Tropical Cyclone Haruna made landfall on the south-west coast of Madagascar. Government officials have reported over 17,000 people have been affected by the storm, with 13 reported deaths, and 1,500 houses destroyed or flooded.

name: Tropical Cyclone Rusty, Australia
description: Major flooding is expected as Tropical Cyclone Rusty moves inland from Western Australia's Pilbara coast and puts new towns on red alert. People in adjacent inland areas, including Marble Bar, were warned to go to shelter immediately.

name: Earthquake in South Eastern Iran
description: A powerful earthquake has hit the border regions between Iran and Pakistan. The USGS measured the earthquake at magnitude 7.8, located 50 miles east-south-east of the town of Khash. It is the biggest earthquake in Iran for 40 years.

name: Boston Marathon Bombing
description: Two powerful bombs exploded near the finish line of the Boston Marathon on Monday afternoon, killing three people, including an 8-year-old child, and injuring over 100 people.

name: Flooding in Nigeria
description: Flooding in two areas of northern Nigeria has killed at least 11 people and displaced hundreds, officials and residents said Friday, the latest casualties in the country's rainy season.

name: Earthquake in Yunnan Province, China
description: A shallow 5.5-magnitude earthquake hit southwest China on Sunday, causing 700 homes to collapse and leaving 30 people injured, state media said.

name: Explosion in West Texas
description: A massive explosion at a fertilizer plant in the town of West Texas has left up to 15 people dead and more than 150 people injured. The blast registered as a 2.1 earthquake according to federal seismologists.

name: Earthquake in China
description: A powerful earthquake has killed at least 160 people and injured at least 5,700 in China's rural south-west, officials say.

name: Building Collapse in Dhaka, Bangladesh
description: At least 87 people have been killed and many others trapped after an eight-storey building housing garment factories collapsed outside the capital, Dhaka.

name: Canada-Red River Flooding
description: A potential for exceeding moderate and major river flood levels exists for the Red River of the North.

name: Earthquake in Myanmar
description: A strong earthquake collapsed a bridge and damaged ancient Buddhist pagodas in northern Myanmar, and piecemeal reports from the underdeveloped mining region said mines collapsed and as many as 12 people were feared dead.

name: Floods in England
description: Over 800 residences across England and Wales have been inundated as a barrage of rain and winds have pounded Britain.  The Prime Minister has vowed to assist communities in southwestern England and the Midlands, which are recuperating from floods.

name: Tropical Cyclone Bopha
description: Tropical Cyclone Bopha gained strength Monday, becoming a super typhoon with sustained winds greater than 150 mph (240 kph) -- the equivalent of a Category 5 hurricane in the Atlantic Ocean.

name: Ash Creek Fire, Montana
description: Weather conditions are shaping up to test firefighters Tuesday in southeast Montana as they continue to battle the Ash Creek Fire. The lightning-sparked wildfire has now burned an estimated 186,000 acres, and is about 55% contained as of Tuesday.

name: Wildfires in California
description: Nine major fires are currently burning across California.  Scott's Fire has burned  4,618 acres and threatens 300 homes.  1,300 firefighters simultaneously battle the Sixteen Complex fire.

name: Cyclone Giovanna
description: A tropical cyclone has hit the island of Madagascar, with winds of up to 194km (120mph) ripping up trees and electricity pylons.

name: Floods, Landslides in Philippines
description:
Coastal communities were devastated early on Saturday in flash floods triggered by a tropical storm.
More than 650 people were killed and another 800 people are still missing.

name: Floods in Mozambique
description: Mozambique has started to evacuate some 55,000 people after heavy rains caused sea levels to rise to dangerous levels in parts of the country, officials say. The worst affected areas are in the southern Gaza province.

name: Hurricane Sandy, East Coast USA
description: Shelters opened and tens of thousands of people were ordered to evacuate coastal areas as people across the Northeast prepare for Hurricane Sandy, which threatens 50 million people along the most heavily populated corridor in the nation.

name: Earthquake in Iran
description: A 5.5 magnitude earthquake hit Iran's Zohan district at 8:38 on Wednesday evening. Five villages were destroyed and at least 11 others damaged, according to Iran's crisis management organisation.

name: Queensland Flooding
description: Rain brought by Tropical Cyclone Oswald has caused major flooding in Queensland, Australia. Rescuers are trying to reach hundreds of people stranded in the city of Bundaberg and more than 200,000 people are without power across the state.

name: Hugo Chavez State Funeral
description: Hugo Chavez, who led Venezuela for 14 years, died on Tuesday, March 5th aged 58 after a long battle with cancer. After the funeral, Mr Chavez's body will be taken to a military museum to lie in state for another seven days.
